10/06/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- High Representative Christian Schwarz-Schilling has begun consultations with the leaders of the BiH political parties on the issue of constitutional reform. The closed-door talks are aimed at clarifying the stances of local leaders and getting the process back under way, a spokesperson for Schwarz-Schilling said. 
The top international envoy plans to address the BiH Parliament's two chambers at a plenary session on Wednesday (June 13th). (Nezavisne Novine - 10/06/07; Dnevni Avaz, Nezavisne Novine - 09/06/07; RTRS - 08/06/07)
